               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; four groups of lines on the incipit page of the text I-3; incipit lines of the miracles; name of the original donor; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numbers.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles are introduced with word taʔammǝr “miracle”, mǝʿǝraf “chapter”, zǝkr “memory”, nagar “speech”.</note>
                     <note>The miracles are numbered, with a few mistakes. The miracles introduced with the word mǝʿǝraf “chapter” are mostly not numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="151r"/>Fol. 151r: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘተሣየጥዋ፡ በወርቆሙ፡ ሕዝበ፡ ዘአቅሐረይቶ፡ ወመድኅንሂ፡ ዘወልደት፡ ጐነፅ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞ ሙ፡ ውስተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>Fol. 151r: A statement that the manuscript belongs to (the church of?) Qǝddus Mikaʾel and that it was bought by the people of ʾAqḥaräyto. Fol. 151v: A statement that the manuscript belongs to (the church of?) Qǝddus Mikaʾel of ʾAqḥaräyto and that it was commissioned and acquired at the time of the office of Ḫabtä Giyorgis, father of Wälda Gabr, whose wife was Wälättä Haymanot, and brother of Zägiyorgis.</note>
                     </colophon>
